                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.512/70: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Tangier</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Blake</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-05T10:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 5, 1929—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 5—7:49 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Your telegram No. 4, January 22, 6 p.m. Conditions Department’s assent mailed
                    French Resident General January 25, 1929.<note n="57" xml:id="d599fn57">Note
                        dated January 23, 1929.</note> Latter telegraphed me January 30, 1929;
                    taxation referred to becomes applicable February 1st. All the measures
                    definitely adopted without amendment in December sessions Legislative Assembly.
                    Promulgation by Sultan’s representative on January 31st and countersignature
                    President Committee of Control gave them executive authority. Enforcement gate
                    tax delayed by adjustment of administrative dispositions until yesterday.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blake</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
